This topic describes how to install and configure the Black Duck Hub Service Broker for PCF.

1. Download the Black Duck Hub Service Broker for PCF product file from <a href='https://network.pivotal.io/products/black-duck-hub-service-broker'>Pivotal Network</a>.

1. Navigate to the **Ops Manager Installation Dashboard**, and click **Import a Product** to upload the product file. 

1. Under **Import a Product**, click **+** next to the version number of the Black Duck Hub Service Broker for PCF. 
This adds the tile to your staging area.

1. Click the newly-added **Black Duck Hub Service Broker** tile.  
    <img src='images/pcf-tile.png' alt='Black Duck Hub Service Broker tile'></img>    

1. Select **Black Duck Hub Credentials** in the left navigation column, and update the following fields:  
   * **Hub access protocol**
   * **Hub network address**
   * **Hub port**  
   * **Hub Username and Password**
   * **Ignore TLS/SSL errors** (enabling this is strongly discouraged)
   <img src='images/tile-config-1.0.1.png'></img>


1. Click **Save**.

1. Return to the **Ops Manager Installation Dashboard**, and click **Apply Changes** to install the Black Duck Hub Service Broker for PCF tile.

